<ghayward@jhmi.edu>

[There is significant diversity of herpesviruses within elephants, as
within most well investigated mammals. A recent study described an
additional 4 elephantid herpesviruses; see
<http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/sites/entrez?Db=pubmed&Cmd=ShowDetailView&TermToSearch=17884307>.
This is indeed sad, and another disease that we don't know enough about to
prevent or adequately treat. - Mod.TG

Calgary, in the south of the province of Alberta, can be located on the
HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Canada at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?g=5913490&v=51.05,-114.085,5>. - CopyEd.MJ]
